commitResults.messageBody:
Currently we don't know how the contact relates to the
organisation.

A role field will inform the user of the role the contact plays
for the organisation, whether it be mentor, mentee, admin, etc.

Centre is a field for the Student and Mentor classes that has
not been added yet.

Through this field, the user will be able to see which centre
the Students and Mentors are assigned to.

It will make it easier to find which mentors and students are
in a particular centre.

Users can now input the centre and can see all the listed
relevant mentors and students.

Role was changed in the upstream branch
such that it is a String value now. Edits have been
made to reflect that.

Now role is a string instead of a class for better
encapsulation.

Could not add a contact with the proper role,
need to use MENTOR or STUDENT (case sensitive).

Could not edit because it defaults back to PERSON role.
Made the change in the EditCommand to maintain the
contacts' role.

Currently users need to scroll through
to find particular roles.

With this command, if a user wants to filter a
specific role, they can just input and see all
those with those roles. Currently ony works for
Mentor, Student and Person.

Was implemented before as findbyloc.

Recovered and renamed. Now users can find
contacts in a specific address.

Currently, its hard to find all the students a mentor has.
We would need to go through all the contacts.

With this command, we can easily list out all the students
a mentor is matched to when we want to check that.

Shows the class diagram for person, student and
mentor.

Mentor and student are shown to be subclasses
of person with extra fields.
Correct attribute visibility in model class diagram

Help command was showing the previous AB3
user guide. Due to the changes we made to the
AB3, we had to update the user guide and therefore
update to the new link.

Now with the new link, users who need help in the
address book can look at our updated user guide.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix blank spaces in the gui
commitResults.messageBody:
Before, there were blank spaces in the person card
for remarks and mentors. This is ugly to look at.

Now its nicer and cleaner.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix invalid text for match command
commitResults.messageBody:
The invalid text for this was add command
as a placeholder. However, users unfamiliar with
the command would not know how to use the
match command.

Now with it updated, users can see properly
how to utilise the match command.

Similar to match, this was the add
invalid comment as a placeholder.

Now users can know how to use the unmatch
command.

Last time, we could edit role. However, we changed
the behaviour so that we cannot edit role. Therefore,
we must remove any residue from that time. edit 1 r/
was showing that the field cannot be empty instead of an
invalid command format despite it being an invalid command
format.

Now when users try to edit role using r/, the system will show that
its an invalid command format.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix blank space at the bottom
commitResults.messageBody:
Before when a person had a field missing
it would show up as blank space at the bottom
of the person card.

Removing the minHeight now will make it so that
there would be no blank space at the bottom.
Fix blank space at the bottom

Skeleton for the UG commands so
its easier to edit.

to avoid false positives.
